Not if they are chosen by God...

546
00:42:09,210 --> 00:42:12,145
anointed by his righteous prophet-

547
00:42:12,213 --> 00:42:13,976
by you.

548
00:42:15,450 --> 00:42:18,442
You would reject our God?

549
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:21,182
God promised us this land.

550
00:42:21,256 --> 00:42:23,087
This is God's kingdom.

551
00:42:23,158 --> 00:42:25,058
He is our onl king.

552
00:42:25,126 --> 00:42:28,323
You have the ear of the Lord, Samuel

553
00:42:30,098 --> 00:42:33,864
You must ask him to choose a king for us.

554
00:42:37,372 --> 00:42:40,432
Leave me alone. All of you.

555
00:42:43,011 --> 00:42:45,536
[ SamueI ]
I have given everything.

556
00:42:46,881 --> 00:42:49,111
Now they have rejected me...

557
00:42:50,118 --> 00:42:52,518
and you, God.

558
00:42:52,587 --> 00:42:56,318
But if you say
I should give them a king...

559
00:42:56,391 --> 00:42:59,189
then of course I will .

560
00:43:02,263 --> 00:43:04,697
But who should it be?

561
00:43:07,002 --> 00:43:09,232
[ Wind Rushing ]

562
00:43:17,512 --> 00:43:19,446
[ Whinnying ]

563
00:43:23,151 --> 00:43:24,641
I see...

564
00:43:26,888 --> 00:43:28,981
that could never be me.

565
00:43:37,465 --> 00:43:39,933
But I will still be your prophet.

566
00:43:41,603 --> 00:43:44,401
I can guide your king.

567
00:43:44,472 --> 00:43:47,771
[ Crowd Shouting ]
Saul! Saul! Saul!

568
00:43:47,842 --> 00:43:50,743
Saul! Saul! Saul!

569
00:43:50,812 --> 00:43:53,076
[ Crowd Cheering ]

570
00:43:54,949 --> 00:43:57,747
[ Chanting ]
Saul! Saul! Saul!

571
00:43:57,819 --> 00:44:01,653
[ Chanting Continues ]

572
00:44:05,660 --> 00:44:07,184
Saul

573
00:44:08,396 --> 00:44:12,833
May you reign justl and wisel ...

574
00:44:12,901 --> 00:44:15,392
and according to God's law.

575
00:44:18,473 --> 00:44:23,877
I anoint you the first king of Israel

576
00:44:29,851 --> 00:44:33,412
May I, as God's prophet...

577
00:44:33,488 --> 00:44:36,286
help you in any way I can.

578
00:44:39,027 --> 00:44:42,394
[ Narrator ] A new era
in Israelite history is beginning-

579
00:44:42,464 --> 00:44:47,128
- [ Chanting ] Saul! Saul!
- the perlod of prophets and kings.

580
00:44:49,204 --> 00:44:53,698
They must work together
to secure the promised land.

581
00:44:53,775 --> 00:44:57,006
[ Crowd Chanting ]
Saul! Saul! Saul!

582
00:44:57,078 --> 00:44:59,103
Next time on The Bible .

583
00:44:59,180 --> 00:45:01,774
- [ Horse Whinnies ]
- [ SauI ] Are the men ready?

584
00:45:01,850 --> 00:45:03,579
They're ready.

585
00:45:03,651 --> 00:45:05,812
We must make a sacrifice before we attack.

586
00:45:06,921 --> 00:45:08,582
[ SamueI ]
May God forgive you!

587
00:45:08,656 --> 00:45:11,591
Be a king. Leave the job of priest to me.

588
00:45:11,659 --> 00:45:16,153
You are our prophet, but I am your king!

589
00:45:16,231 --> 00:45:19,496
What the Lord gives, he can take away.

590
00:45:19,567 --> 00:45:22,161
God is with me!

591
00:45:22,237 --> 00:45:25,331
Are you with him, Lord, really?

592
00:45:25,406 --> 00:45:27,397
You disobeyed the Lord.

593
00:45:27,475 --> 00:45:31,172
He has torn your kingdom from you
and given lt to Davld .

594
00:45:31,246 --> 00:45:35,148
When you have my crown, will you not
kill my descendants, bury my name?

595
00:45:35,216 --> 00:45:38,811
[ David ]
Jerusalem, our new home.

596
00:45:38,887 --> 00:45:41,549
[ Men Shouting ]

597
00:45:42,624 --> 00:45:44,615
[ Man ]
A king is never above his god.

598
00:45:44,692 --> 00:45:46,683
You abused your power.

599
00:45:46,761 --> 00:45:49,662
You took everything
from your most loyal servant.

600
00:45:49,731 --> 00:45:53,189
You took his wife, then you took his life.

601
00:45:53,268 --> 00:45:55,293
You think God doesn't see everything?

602
00:45:55,370 --> 00:45:57,065
I am his chosen one.

603
00:45:57,138 --> 00:46:00,539
Davld , he will bring disaster
on your house.

604
00:46:00,608 --> 00:46:02,235
We shall see.

